-VARIABLES:

$ -> Variable designation (Every time you create or use a variable you use it, it serves to ID something as a variable not just inicialize it)
|-> $Name_of_Variable  = 25;
|-> $Name_of_Variable2 = "this is a string";
|-> $Name_of_Variable3 = null;

const name_of_Variable4 = 123.1 -> a const variable does not use $

NOTE: A variable can be of any type all the time, a variable that has been given an int can later become a string for example
NOTE: Devs may use camelCase on variable names, as in the names are based on what the variable is for and it uses thisName kind of format, starting with lower case and upper case later

COMMANDS:
isset($var);   -> Checks if a variable exists
empty($var);   -> Checks if a variable is empty
unset($var);   -> Deletes a variable
gettype($var); -> Checks what data type the variable is
is_int($var);  -> Self Explanatory, it checks if $var is of int data type
is_string($var);
is_bool($var);
in_array($var);


CONVERSION DATA TYPES
$var = (int)"25"; -> will turn 25 from a string into an integer



