-ARRAYS:

NOTE: Basic arrays Works much the same way as C++
NOTE: In PHP arrays can have several data types at the same time

--MAPPED ARRAYS
NOTE: PHP has a combination of C++ basic arrays and Maps

$Variable = ["name" => "Kile",
             "Number" => 25,
             "stuff" => "blah"]; 
              |-> Key      |-> Value

COMMANDS:
$array[] = "something";              -> add to the end of the array
array_push($array, "this", "that");  -> Add several things to end of array
array_pop($array);                   -> Remove last item
array_shift($array);                 -> Remove first item
unset($array[1]);                    -> Remove Specific index
is_array("value", $array)            -> Checks if something exists inside an array
array_search("value", $array);       -> returns index of the value if found
count($array)                        -> .size()
array_keys($array)                   -> gets all the keys
array_values($array)                 -> gets all values
array_merge($arrayA, $arrayB)        -> Merges the contents of 2 arrays together
sort($array)                         -> Sort the array ascending
rsort($array)                        -> sort the array descending
